install neo4j
https://debian.neo4j.org/?_ga=2.180534247.153130316.1570995946-1723945139.1570995946
run 'neo4j console' to start the server.

start bloodhound './BloodHound --no-sandbox'
https://github.com/BloodHoundAD/BloodHound/releases

run sharphound.exe from remote server to enumerate AD, GPO etc to JSON files
import the JSON files to BloodHound and run queries to see the mapped graph.
